333 //Using the extended script system we first create a list of viable spells
334 SpellInfo const* apSpell[MAX_CREATURE_SPELLS];
335 memset(apSpell, 0, MAX_CREATURE_SPELLS * sizeof(SpellInfo*));
336
337 uint32 spellCount = 0;
338
339 SpellInfo const* tempSpell = nullptr;
340
341 //Check if each spell is viable(set it to null if not)
342 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_CREATURE_SPELLS; i++)
343 {
344 tempSpell = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(me->m_spells[i]);
345
346 //This spell doesn't exist
347 if (!tempSpell)
348 continue;
349
350 // Targets and Effects checked first as most used restrictions
351 //Check the spell targets if specified
352 if (targets && !(SpellSummary[me->m_spells[i]].Targets & (1 << (targets - 1))))
353 continue;
354
355 //Check the type of spell if we are looking for a specific spell type
356 if (effects && !(SpellSummary[me->m_spells[i]].Effects & (1 << (effects - 1))))
357 continue;
358
359 //Check for school if specified
360 if (school && (tempSpell->SchoolMask & school) == 0)
361 continue;
362
363 //Check for spell mechanic if specified
364 if (mechanic && tempSpell->Mechanic != mechanic)
365 continue;
366
367 //Make sure that the spell uses the requested amount of power
368 if (powerCostMin && tempSpell->ManaCost < powerCostMin)
369 continue;
370
371 if (powerCostMax && tempSpell->ManaCost > powerCostMax)
372 continue;
373
374 //Continue if we don't have the mana to actually cast this spell
375 if (tempSpell->ManaCost > me->GetPower(Powers(tempSpell->PowerType)))
376 continue;
377
378 //Check if the spell meets our range requirements
379 if (rangeMin && me->GetSpellMinRangeForTarget(target, tempSpell) < rangeMin)
380 continue;
381 if (rangeMax && me->GetSpellMaxRangeForTarget(target, tempSpell) > rangeMax)
382 continue;
383
384 //Check if our target is in range
385 if (me->IsWithinDistInMap(target, float(me->GetSpellMinRangeForTarget(target, tempSpell))) || !me->IsWithinDistInMap(target, float(me->GetSpellMaxRangeForTarget(target, tempSpell))))
386 continue;
387
388 //All good so lets add it to the spell list
389 apSpell[spellCount] = tempSpell;
390 ++spellCount;
391 }
392
393 //We got our usable spells so now lets randomly pick one
394 if (!spellCount)
395 return nullptr;
396
397 return apSpell[urand(0, spellCount - 1)];
398}
